Small things I'd like to see added to Blitz2:

  * Free Pizza tokens with every BUM.
  * The ASL screen requester should come up configured to the current
    screens settings. Hitting OK with the default parameters returns
    an incorrect ViewMode of 0.
  * Better support for adding copper instructions to clists generated
    using the new display library. The ability to get the address of the
    instruction inserted so that instructions can be modified every frame
    if so desired.
  * Strings that work.

Large things I'd like to see added to Blitz2:

  * NEW TED (WB 2/3)
  * LINKER
  * 68020 SUPPORT


I think the new commands this issue are OK, but more time should be
spent getting the existing commands working !

