WHERE CREDIT IS DUE
Personally I think that allowing your users to get upgraded libraries
(or DEFLIB file) directly from the authors of various commands is a
bad idea. Imagine the incompatability problems that may arise due
to different users having different versions of commands from different
authors.
I think that any library extensions should be released through ACID who
can keep a constant check on the quality of any new additions. I think
that the way things work at the moment with BUM subscribers receiving
the latest stuff is great. If it works why break it ?

